      "old_string": "### Device Control Flow\n\nThe Shrooly device exposes a local REST API at `http://192.168.1.18`. To change settings, ShroomHub calls the device directly from the **user's browser** (same local network). The backend API only stores sensor data \u2014 it does NOT proxy device commands.\n\n**Important:** Device control only works when the user is on the same WiFi network as the Shrooly. The UI should detect this and show a clear message when the device is unreachable.",
      "new_string": "### Device Control Flow\n\nDevice control works **remotely** via a command queue:\n\n1. Dashboard sends `POST /api/commands` to api-shrooms with `{endpoint, value}`\n2. Server queues the command in `device_commands` table (status: pending)\n3. Shrooly polls `POST /api/commands/pending` every 60s\n4. Server returns one pending command, marks as \"sent\"\n5. Shrooly applies the setting locally\n\nThis means the dashboard works from **anywhere** \u2014 no local network required.\n\n**16 remotely controllable endpoints:**\n`target_humidity`, `humidifier__speed`, `humidity_hysteresis`, `temperature_target`, `temperature_hysteresis`, `temperature_warning_minimum`, `temperature_warning_maximum`, `air_exchange__period__min_`, `air_exchange__run_duration__s_`, `air_exchange__speed`, `lights__sunrise_hour`, `lights__duration__hours_`, `white_led_intensity`, `red_led_intensity`, `green_led_intensity`, `blue_led_intensity`",
